Essex was born in or about 1765 at Coventry, Warwickshire, the son of Timothy Essex there; Margaret Essex was his sister.
In 1786 he established himself as a teacher of the pianoforte, organ, and flute.
In order to better his position he matriculated at Oxford as a member of Magdalen Hall 10 December 1806, and took the degree of bachelor of music on the following 17 December.

He proceeded doctor of music 2 December 1812.
He died 27 September 1847, aged 82, in York Buildings, New Road, London.
